'''Callum Kyle Harriott''' (born 4 March 1994) is an [[English people|English]] [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Charlton Athletic F.C.|Charlton Athletic]] as a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]]. He is product of the Charlton Athletic academy.

==Career==
Born in [[Norbury]], Callum attended St.Andrew Church of England High School in [[London Borough of Croydon|Croydon]]. Harriott made his debut for the Addicks on 25 April 2011 in a [[Football League One|League One]] game against [[Rochdale A.F.C.|Rochdale]] at [[The Valley (London)|The Valley]], which ended in a 3<U+2013>1 win for Charlton. He came on as a late substitute for loanee [[Dean Parrett]].<ref>{{Cite news |url= http://www.cafctv.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0,,10267~2347316,00.html |title=Callum's quest |date=2011-04-27 |accessdate=2011-04-31}}</ref> He then started his first game for the club two days later on the last game of the 2010-11 season against [[Hartlepool United|Hartlepool]].<ref>{{Cite news |url= http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/13247306 |title=Charlton 0-0 Hartlepool |date=7 May 2011 |accessdate=24 May 2013}}</ref>

Although he did not feature for the Charlton first-team in their 2011-12 promotion season, he made his [[Football Championship|Championship]] debut after coming off the bench as a 74th minute substitute for fellow academy graduate [[Scott Wagstaff]] in a 2-1 win against [[Blackpool F.C.|Blackpool]].<ref>{{Cite news |url= http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/20919213 |title=Charlton 2-1 Blackpool |date=12 January 2013 |accessdate=24 May 2013}}</ref> He then scored his first senior goal on 9 March 2013, in a 1-0 win away to [[Huddersfield Town F.C.|Huddersfield Town]].<ref>[http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/21639315 "Huddersfield 0-1 Charlton"] BBC Sport. 9 March 2013. Retrieved 9 March 2013.</ref> He scored his second goal for Charlton in a record-breaking 6-0 away win for the Addicks against [[Barnsley F.C.|Barnsley]] on 13 April 2013.<ref name="Barnsley 0-6 Charlton">{{cite news|title=Barnsley 0-6 Charlton|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/22049624|publisher=BBC Sport|date=17 May 2013|accessdate=24 May 2013}}</ref> Harriott was one of the six different scorers for Charlton that match.<ref name="Barnsley 0-6 Charlton"/> On 17 May 2013, Harriott signed a new three year contract with the club.<ref>{{cite news|title=Charlton Athletic: Dorian Dervite & Callum Harriott extend deals|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/22572654|publisher=BBC Sport|date=17 May 2013|accessdate=18 May 2013}}</ref>

==International career==
On 2 May 2013, Harriot was named in manager [[Noel Blake]]'s [[England national under-19 football team|England under-19]] team to face Belgium, Georgia and Scotland in the [[2013 UEFA European Under-19 Football Championship elite qualification|2013 UEFA European Under-19 qualification round]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thefa.com/england/mens-u19s/News/2013/elite-round-squad-announced-020513|title=U19s Elite Squad Named|publisher=The Football Association|work=TheFA.com.|date=2 May 2013|accessdate=7 May 2013}}</ref>

